items.definition: The Great Barrier Reef Marine Park Authority advises the Australian Government on the care and development of the Great Barrier Reef Marine Park. The Authority provides for the long-term protection, ecologically sustainable use, understanding and enjoyment of the Great Barrier Reef for all Australian communities through the care and development of the Marine Park.

prefLabel._value: Great Barrier Reef Marine Park Authority (GBRMPA)

items.definition: Australian Marine Ecology Pty Ltd is a scientific organisation that specialises in marine ecological research and consulting with an emphasis on quantitative field studies.
Fathom Pacific provides aquatic scientific services for industry, government and research agencies.
Infotech Research was founded in 1985 as a technically focused management consultancy, working in R&D, business planning, occupational health, cleaner production energy and environmental management.
NRL is the corporate research laboratory for the Navy and Marine Corps and conducts a broad program of scientific research, technology and advanced development.

The Federal University of Sao Paulo (Portuguese: Universidade Federal de Sao Paulo, UNIFESP) is a university in the state of Sao Paulo, Brazil. It was founded in 1933. The University has six campuses in Sao Paulo,  and four more in Guarulhos,Diadema, Santos, Sao Jose dos Compos and Osasco. (Courtesy of Wikipedia)
The Institute of the Sea is found on the Baixada Santista campus in Sao Paulo.

prefLabel._value: Instituto Do Mar, Federal University of Sao Paulo (UNIFESP)

items.definition: The Federal University of Santa Catarina (Portuguese: Universidade Federal de Santa Catarina, UFSC) is a public university in Florianopolis, the capital city of Santa Catarina in southern Brazil. It was established in 1960. (Courtesy of Wikipedia)
The Department of Aquaculture was created in 1984, and is part of the School of Agricultural Sciences.

prefLabel._value: Department of Aquaculture, Federal University of Santa Catarina (UFSC)

items.definition: Wollongong city is located 80km south of Sydney. It covers 714 square kilometres and occupies a narrow coastal strip bordered by the Royal National Park to the north, Lake Illawarra to the south, the Pacific Ocean to the east, and the Illawarra escarpment to the west.
